ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thank you very much. We have updated our Alta Rica packaging with a new jar and label design, but please be assured we have not made any changes to the recipe itself. We've made a note of your comments though & they'll be passed to the rest of the team.

Results.ReviewText: Last month I bought two jars of Alta Rica with the new jar design and label. What a disappointment – little wonder they were on special offer. The coffee tastes cheap and muddy and not at all like the Alta Rica I've been drinking and enjoying for many years. I notice that Nescafe/Nestle are saying that the formulation hasn't changed.  Fortunately, I tend to stock up on coffee and so still have some jars of the previous design and label in the cupboard. Doing a like-for-like test, I find it difficult to take seriously the assertion that only the jar/label has changed and so have ceased to buy Alta Rica and will look for an alternative. In the meantime, my older stocks will keep me going for another month.
Results.Title: No longer my cup of coffee

ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thanks for leaving us a review. We've not made any changes to the recipe of NESCAFÉ Alta Rica, we've only updated the jar design. If you're concerned about the taste of your coffee, please give one of the team a call on 0800 58 57 59 so we can look into this.

Results.ReviewText:
While I generally drink "proper" coffee (espresso/stove top/pour-over), I have always kept Alta Rica for a kick-start to the morning when I just don't have time to grind and brew from scratch.

I have to agree with other recent reviewers in that the recent changes are NOT just to packaging. Aroma and flavour have both changed significantly, and for the worse.

If this is not a change to the blend/product by Nescafe, then it is either poor quality control or some detrimental effect of the new packaging.
Results.Title: New...and Ruined

Results.ReviewText:
I've been drinking Alta Rica for, well, years, it must be close to a decade now, I always have at least 3 cups a day and unless the water has gone "off" in the kettle, it's always tasted great, until the new packaging.
It really has changed in flavour and aroma, as others have said, it can't be a coincidence that so many people have noticed this, surely? Even my mum and her friend who love Alta rica, are no longer drinking it.
And why fix what isn't broken? the former jar design was perfect and easy to spot.
Results.Title: New jar/design, but definitely a drop in taste!

Results.ReviewText: I have enjoyed Nescafe Alta Rica coffee for years.  It had slightly edgier flavour which I preferred to richer or lighter options.  It was slightly bitter if anything.  It has changed recently and I don't like it any more.  It seems to be trying to be like an Americano you would get out somewhere.  Also, there was a foil lid inside the screw top with a tab you pulled for a short while.  This was amazing, but it's gone.

Results.ReviewText: I love the Alta Rica Coffee,  I was looking recently for the perfect coffee and I found Alta Rica in my search and it was spot on with its smooth dark taste just right for the first cup of the morning or in fact any time of the day or night the aroma is so exciting  so refreshing and intoxicatingly brilliant. .So easy to prepare, I add a good teaspoonful in a cup add hot water and stir and because I do not take sugar or milk in my coffee I can enjoy its full flavour then just sit back relax and enjoy this amazing coffee.

Results.ReviewText: I like strong bold coffee. Especially on a rainy sunday morning. Ive been around the block with other brands that make false promises. It didnt have that bitter after taste like most instant coffee. Its name is Alta Rica
